<sections><clause id="_6caaec55-54df-4bc0-96e1-5b4ad6a8fd17" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative" displayorder="1">

<p id="_6324be19-d845-4b52-8bf2-fb890af38e86">
<strong><sup>87</sup>Rb atom, crossover transition between the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>d</mi></math></stem> and <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi></math></stem> hyperfine components of the saturated absorption at <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>780</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_nm"><mi mathvariant="normal">nm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem> (D2 transition)</strong>
</p>
</clause>
<clause id="_recommended_value_of_the_frequency" obligation="normative" displayorder="2"><title depth="1">1.<tab/>Recommended value <eref type="inline" bibitemid="ci2015" citeas="[1]">[1]</eref> of the frequency:</title><p id="_8a6042fc-c444-4762-bb32-94d08b092d29">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>87</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mtext>Rb</mtext></mrow><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>f</mi><mtext>&#160;</mtext><mi>c</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>384&#8239;227&#8239;981.9</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_MHz"><mi mathvariant="normal">MHz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_43d2d154-2fc0-4c12-8d88-9cc49780fbff">equivalent to</p>
<p id="_b9c5939f-ccc0-4240-912d-745c3dc112f5"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>87</mn></mrow></msup><msub><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>R</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>f</mi><mtext>&#160;</mtext><mi>c</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>780&#8239;246&#8239;291.6</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>,</p>
<p id="_a48982ff-7156-4dde-a588-6dfeaef9927f">with an estimated relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem> applies to the radiation of a tunable Extended Cavity Diode Laser, stabilized to the <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>d</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>f</mi></math></stem> saturated absorption line in a well characterized magnetically shielded rubidium absorption cell by the third-harmonic technique,</p>
<ul id="_b8637bb4-7390-474e-ac5a-a329f2604bb9">
<li>
<p id="_8aecf90f-851d-4bd3-a4fe-b53b5b581866">cell temperature <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mn>22.5</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu23"><mi mathvariant="normal">&#176;C</mi></mrow>









</math></stem></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="_78e2e10d-2be2-4e81-9bd9-b794e23784b5">frequency modulation width, peak-to-peak, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_MHz"><mi mathvariant="normal">MHz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>;</p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="_c299dc3f-06f3-4a72-8b48-200b7f223fe8">saturating beam intensity of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><mn>120</mn><mo>&#177;</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_mW.cm-2"><mi mathvariant="normal">mW</mi><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">cm</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow>









</math></stem></p>
</li>
</ul></clause>
